Clicking it opens the Start Menu, which provides access to various system functions and installed applications.

- **Custom:** This option allows advanced users to choose specific components and settings for installation.

The "Destination Directory" field, displaying "C:\Program Files\Netscape\Communicator", indicates where the software will be installed. A "Browse..." button is available to change this location if desired.

- **< Back:** Allows the user to return to the previous step of the installation process.
- **Next >:**  Proceeds to the next step of the installation process.
- **Cancel:**  Aborts the installation process.

* **"Make Netscape Communicator my default Internet browser"**: Selecting this option will make Netscape Communicator the primary browser used for opening web pages.
* **"Make Netscape.com my home page"**:  This option sets Netscape.com as the website that automatically loads upon opening the browser.
* **"Use Netscape.com to search the Web"**: Enabling this will configure Netscape.com as the default search engine within the browser.

All three checkboxes are currently selected with a checkmark.

* **"< Back"**: This button likely allows the user to navigate back to a previous step in the installation process.
* **"Next >"**: This button, highlighted in blue, proceeds to the next stage of the installation.
* **"Cancel"**: Clicking this button will likely halt the installation process.

Below, a list titled "Existing Folders:" presents alternative directories, such as "Accessories", "Administrative Tools", "Games", and "Startup". Users can click on any of these existing folders to select them as the installation directory.

At the bottom of the window, three buttons offer navigation and control options:

- "< Back": Allows the user to navigate back to a previous step in the installation process.
- "Next >": Proceeds to the next step in the installation process, using the currently displayed or selected program folder. 
- "Cancel":  Halts the installation process and closes the setup window.
